eu.trentorise.opendata.traceprov.dcat

Class ADcatDataset

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.trentorise.opendata.traceprov.dcat.ADcatDataset
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DcatDataset

    @Value.Immutable
abstract class ADcatDataset
extends Object
implements Serializable
    A collection of data, published or curated by a single agent, and available for access or download in one or more formats. Defined by dcat:dataset This class represents the actual dataset as published by the dataset publisher. In cases where a distinction between the actual dataset and its entry in the catalog is necessary (because metadata such as modification date and maintainer might differ), the ADcatCatalogRecord class can be used for the latter.
    Author:
    David Leoni

      • getAccrualPeriodicity

        @Value.Default
public String getAccrualPeriodicity()
        The frequency at which dataset is published, as defined by dct: accrualPeriodicity

        In this implementation, returned format could be either

        • A String encoded in ISO 8601 Duration format, like i.e. P3Y6M4DT12H30M5S
          • This format can be used when periodicity can be precisely defined (i.e. there is an update every second for sensor data)
        • A string with one of the DCAT AP profile frequency codes, like BIWEEKLY . Note these codes also include special frequencies such as UNKNOWN , IRREGULAR, CONT and UPDATE_CONT
        • A string that can't be parsed as ISO duration nor as DCAT AP frequency codes (i.e. a string in natural language, like 'Every two weeks except during summer'). In this case the string MUST be prepended with "unparseable:"
        • the empty string, in case duration is unspecified

      • getIssued

        @Value.Default
public String getIssued()
        Date of formal issuance (e.g., publication) of the dataset. Note Dcat standard requires dates in string format to be ISO 8601 Date and Time compliant string format i.e. "2011-12-11". In TraceProv if date format is unknown prepend it with "unparseable:" to avoid confusing it with regular dates. If date is unknown the empty string is used.

      • getLandingPage

        @Value.Default
public String getLandingPage()
        A Web page that can be navigated to in a Web browser to gain access to the dataset, its distributions and/or additional information. If the distribution(s) are accessible only through a landing page (i.e. direct download URLs are not known), then the landing page link SHOULD be duplicated as accessURL on a distribution. For relation with ADcatDistribution.getAccessURL() and ADcatDistribution.getDownloadURL() see official dcat documentation

      • getLanguages

        public abstract List<Locale> getLanguages()
        The language of the dataset. This overrides the value of the catalog language in case of conflict. If the dataset is available in multiple languages, use multiple values for this property. If each language is available separately, define an instance of DcatDistribution for each language and describe the specific language of each distribution (i.e. the dataset will have multiple language values from getLanguages() and each distribution will have one of these languages as value of its ADcatDistribution.getLanguage() property). Java Locale should be created out of Language codes defined by the Library of Congress ( ISO 639-1, ISO 639-2)... If a ISO 639-1 (two-letter) code is defined for language, then its corresponding IRI should be used; if no ISO 639-1 code is defined, then IRI corresponding to the ISO 639-2 (three-letter) code should be used.

      • getModified

        @Value.Default
public String getModified()
        Most recent date on which the dataset was changed, updated or modified. The value of this property indicates a change to the actual dataset, not a change to the catalog record. An absent value may indicate that the dataset has never changed after its initial publication, or that the date of last modification is not known, or that the dataset is continuously updated. Note Dcat standard requires dates in string format to be ISO 8601 Date and Time compliant string format i.e. "2011-12-11". In TraceProv if date format is unknown prepend it with ":unparseable" to avoid confusing it with regular dates. If date is unknown the empty string is used.
        See Also:
        getAccrualPeriodicity()

      • getSpatial

        @Value.Default
public GeoJson getSpatial()
        Spatial coverage of the dataset, as specified by dct:spatial i.e. dct:spatial ; The returned object may be either:
        • A GeoJSON object
        • A natural language name inside Feature object
        • a url to an identifier of the location, i.e. http://www.geonames.org/6695072 (in this case you can use Feature.ofId
        • if spatial value is unknwon Feature#of() is returned.

      • getThemes

        public abstract List<SkosConcept> getThemes()
        The main themes of the dataset. A dataset can belong to multiple themes. The set of ASkosConcepts used to categorize the datasets are organized in the ASkosConceptScheme returned by ADcatCatalog.getThemes(). Notice that 'category' is also used as synonym of 'themes' in dcat specs.
